Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil on high heat. Slice the @potatoes{450} into 1cm wide slices (no need to peel). Thinly slice the @portobello mushrooms{2}. Trim the root and the dark green part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways, and then thinly slice widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @carrot{1}, halve lengthways, thinly slice. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into ½cm pieces. Trim the @green beans{150}.

Add the potato and @salt{0.5%tsp} to the boiling water and simmer until tender, 
~{15-20%minutes}. 

> The potato slices are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Once the potato slices are cooked, ladle out some of the cooking water into a #jug{} and set aside, then carefully drain the potato in a #colander{} (don't worry if some break up!).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}, stir and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and season with @black pepper{}. Cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}, stir every minute. Then stir in the leek, carrot and onion. Cook until soft, another ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the reserved potato cooking water.

Stir in the @chicken stock powder{1}, bring the mixture to a simmer then turn the heat to low and simmer until the water has reduced by half, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in the @reduced fat creme fraiche{150}, bring back to the boil and then pour the mixture into a small #ovenproof dish{}. Lay the potato slices on top. Mix the @panko breadcrumbs{25} with some @olive oil{1} and season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle the crumbs on top.

Bake the pie on the top shelf of your oven until the top is golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Meanwhile, refill your potato pan with @water{150} and bring to the boil on high heat with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Once boiling, add in the beans and simmer until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Drain in a colander and then season with black pepper.

Serve your pie in bowls with the green beans alongside and enjoy!